    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Constituent parts of a larger object. A component differs from an item in that the item can stand alone as an independent work but the component typically cannot or does not stand alone. Examples are a panel of a polyptych or a discrete architectural component such as a dome.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
